@endnode

@node HookDisplace "Hook Displace"

HOOK DISPLACE (2.6)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Hook Displace
	 Strength/N,Main/S,Swap/S,Alpha/S,Brush/S,Self/S,
	 XYDelta/S,XYAbsolute/S,Radial/S,HorizOnly/S,VertOnly/S,
	 Grey/S,RGB/S,YMain/S,YSwap/S,YAlpha/S,YBrush/S,YSelf/S

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Run the Displace hook.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Strength@{uu}
	 Strength of the displacement, 1 - 255.

      @{u}Main, Swap, Alpha, Brush, Self@{uu}
	 Source of displacement buffer.

      @{u}XYDelta, XYAbsolute, Radial@{uu}
	 Type of displacement.

      @{u}HorizOnly, VertOnly@{uu}
	 Displace pixels horizontally or vertically only.

      @{u}Grey, RGB@{uu}
	 Treat displacement source buffer as greyscale or separate RGB.

      @{u}YMain, YSwap, YAlpha, YBrush, YSelf@{uu}
	 If provided, the Y axis is displaced from this other buffer.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node HookDream "Hook Dream"

HOOK DREAM (2.0)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Hook Dream Horiz/S,Vert/S,Amount/N,Size/N,Start/N,Phase/N,Wrap/S

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Run the Dream hook.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Horiz, Vert@{uu}
	 Select the direction of the Dream effect.

      @{u}Amount@{uu}
	 Amount of distortion to apply.

      @{u}Size@{uu}
	 Number of waves shown in the picture.

      @{u}Start@{uu}
	 Starting angle (0-360).  For animation purposes.

      @{u}Phase@{uu}
	 Phase (0-360).  For animation purposes.

      @{u}Wrap@{uu}
	 When specified, pixels from one edge of the screen are wrapped
	 around to the other side.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node HookFilmGrain "Hook FilmGrain"

HOOK FILMGRAIN (2.6)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Hook FilmGrain Strength/N,BrightGrain/N,DarkGrain/N,Vary/N,Horiz/S,Vert/S

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Run the FilmGrain hook.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Strength@{uu}
	 Overall strength of noise pattern.  (0 to 255)

      @{u}BrightGrain@{uu}
	 Adjustment to noise strength in bright areas.	(-255 to 255)

      @{u}DarkGrain@{uu}
	 Adjustment to noise strength in dark areas.  (-255 to 255)

      @{u}Vary@{uu}
	 Pixel variance.  0=Vary value, 1=Vary hue,
	 2=Vary value & hue.

      @{u}Horiz, Vert@{uu}
	 Apply noise horizontally or vertically only.
	 If neither is specified, the noise is applied
	 evenly.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node HookFire "Hook Fire"

HOOK FIRE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Hook Fire
	 Seed/N, Increment/N, Length/N, Width/N, Radius/N, X/N, Y/N,
	 Angle/N, Turbulence/N, Density/N, Heat/N,
	 X_Smooth/N, Y_Smooth/N, Paint/S, Add/S, Add_Max/S,
	 Wood/S, Gas/S, Draw1/S, Draw2/S, Draw3/S, Draw4/S,
	 Draw5/S, Draw6/S, Draw7/S, Normal/S, Radial_Out/S, Radial_In/S
	 Style_Palette/S, Blend/N, Taper/N,
	 Blend_Edges/N, Bottom/N, X_Stretch/N, Y_Stretch/N,
	 Speed/N, Variance/N, Wind_Turbulence/N, ANIM_Speed/N,
	 File/F/K

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Run the Fire hook.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Seed@{uu}
	 Random number seed that is used to generate the fire texture.

      @{u}Increment@{uu}
	 Produce later frames of the fire.  (0 to 999)
	 Useful for animations.

      @{u}Length@{uu}
	 How tall the fire is above the fire's base.  (1 to buffer height)

      @{u}Width@{uu}
	 How wide the fire is.	(1 to buffer width)

      @{u}Radius@{uu}
	 Radius of circular fire, from center to fire base.  Only for radial
	 fire.	(0 to 2*buffer height)

      @{u}X@{uu}
	 The x coordinates of the fires center.  (1 to buffer width)

      @{u}Y@{uu}
	 The y coordinates of the fires base.  (1 to buffer height)

      @{u}Angle@{uu}
	 Angle of the fire.  (0 to 360)

      @{u}Turbulence@{uu}
	 The amount of variation in the fire.  (1 to 200)

      @{u}Density@{uu}
	 The soldiness of the fire.  At 255 the fire fills the selected
	 area.	(0 to 255)

      @{u}Heat@{uu}
	 Add or subrtact from the fires temperature.  (-128 to 128)

      @{u}X_Smooth@{uu}
	 Amount of horizontal smoothing of the fire texture.  (-15 to 15)

      @{u}Y_Smooth@{uu}
	 Amount of vertical smoothing of the fire texture.  (-15 to 15)

      @{u}Paint@{uu}
      @{u}Add@{uu}
      @{u}Add_Max@{uu}
	 Mutually exclusive keywords for selecting how the fire's color
	 is added to the buffer.  Paint replaces the buffer color with
	 the fires color.  Add, adds the fire's color to the buffers color.
	 Add_Max, only adds the fire's color to the buffers color when the
	 fire is brighter.

      @{u}Wood@{uu}
      @{u}Gas@{uu}
      @{u}Draw1@{uu}
      @{u}Draw2@{uu}
      @{u}Draw3@{uu}
      @{u}Draw4@{uu}
      @{u}Draw5@{uu}
      @{u}Draw6@{uu}
      @{u}Draw7@{uu}
      @{u}Style_Palette@{uu}
	 Mutually exclusive keywords for selecting which color palette to
	 use.  Wood is a built-in palette for a wood fire.  Gas is a built-in
	 palette for a natural gas fire.  Draw1-7 select from the IFX palettes.
	 And Style_Palette is the colors from the selected Draw1-7 palette
	 that were saved with the other fire parameters.

      @{u}Normal@{uu}
      @{u}Radial_Out@{uu}
      @{u}Radial_In@{uu}
	 Mutually exclusive keywords for selecting between linear fire
	 and radial fire.

      @{u}Blend@{uu}
	 Blends the paint mode colors with the original buffer colors.
	 (0 to 100%)

      @{u}Taper@{uu}
	 Controls the amount of tappering of the top of the fire.  (-100
	 to 100)

      @{u}Blend_Edges@{uu}
	 When coloring using Paint, this does a tappered fading of the
	 fire colors into the buffer colors.  (0 to 100%)

      @{u}Bottom@{uu}
	 How far the fire goes below the fire's base.  (0 to 100% of Length)

      @{u}X_Stretch@{uu}
	 Stretch or compress the fire texture horizontally without changing
	 the fire's size.  (-8 to 8)

      @{u}Y_Stretch@{uu}
	 Stretch or compress the fire texture horizontally without changing
	 the fire's size.  (-8 to 8)

      @{u}Speed@{uu}
	 Constant part of the wind.  Tilts the fire left or right.
	 (-255 to 255)

      @{u}Variance@{uu}
	 Slower and larger variable part of wind.  (0 to 255)

      @{u}Wind_Turbulence@{uu}
	 Faster and smaller scale variable parts of wind.  (0 to 255)

      @{u}ANIM_Speed@{uu}
	 Makes the wind changes happen faster for Variance and
	 Wind_Turbulence.  Works with Increment.  (0 to 40)
	 Useful for animations.

      @{u}File@{uu}
	 Always the last ARexx parameter.  The name of a Fire Load
	 options file.	The options from the file are loaded before the
	 other ARexx inputs are applied.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node HookFXForge "Hook FXForge"

HOOK FXFORGE (3.0)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Hook FXForge
	 RED=R/K, GREEN=G/K, BLUE=B/K, ALPHA=A/K, CONTROL=C/K/N,
	 LOAD/K, DEBUG/K/S

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Run the FXForge hook.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}RED@{uu}
	 Specify the Expression for the Red Channel
	 Note: Enclose the expression in quotes if it contains spaces!

      @{u}GREEN@{uu}
	 Specify the Expression for the Green Channel
	 Note: Enclose the expression in quotes if it contains spaces!

      @{u}BLUE@{uu}
	 Specify the Expression for the Blue Channel
	 Note: Enclose the expression in quotes if it contains spaces!

      @{u}ALPHA@{uu}
	 Specify the Expression for the Alpha Channel
	 Note: Enclose the expression in quotes if it contains spaces!

      @{u}CONTROL@{uu}
	 This option takes *two* parameters.  The Control number followed
	 by the Control value. [CONTROL 2 123 will set Control #2 to 123.]
	 (0 to 7) (0 to 255)

      @{u}LOAD@{uu}
	 Loads the specified effect file.
	 Note: Enclose the filename in quotes if it contains spaces!

      @{u}DEBUG@{uu}
	 Creates a file in RAM: with information about how the expressions
	 are compiled and any run-time errors.

      @{u}NOTES:@{uu}
	  Default values for controls and expresssions are read from environment
	  variables set when the hook is run from the GUI.  If no environment
	  variables are available, controls are set to 0 and the expressions are
	  set to "R", "G", "B" and "A".

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node HookGaussianBlur "Hook GaussianBlur"

HOOK GAUSSIANBLUR (2.6)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Hook GaussianBlur Sigma,FWHM/K,Radius/N,Blend/N,Alpha/S,Swap/S

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Run the GaussianBlur hook.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Sigma@{uu}
	 The Gaussian width of the Gaussian, expressed as a floating point number
	 between 0.1 and 10.0.	(Default 1.0.)

      @{u}FWHM@{uu}
	 The Full Width at Half Maximum of the Gaussian, expressed as a floating
	 point number between 0.1 and 10.0.  Only one of FWHM and Sigma should be
	 specified.

      @{u}Radius@{uu}
	 The Radius/Sigma for the Gaussian, an integer between 1 and 3.
	 (Default 2.)

      @{u}Blend@{uu}
	 The blend between the blurred pixel value and the original pixel value,
	 expressed as a percentage between 0 and 100.  100 indicates that each pixel is
	 completely replaced by the value resulting from the Gaussian blurring.  0
	 indicates that each pixel should retain its original value.  (Default 100.)

      @{u}Alpha@{uu}
	 Use the Alpha buffer as the source for the Gaussian widths.  Sigma or FWHM
	 will be the Gaussian width that corresponds to a white pixel in the Alpha
	 buffer.

      @{u}Swap@{uu}
	 Use the Swap buffer as the source for the Gaussian widths.  Sigma or FWHM will
	 be the Gaussian width that corresponds to a white pixel in the Alpha buffer.
	 Only one of Alpha or Sigma should be specified.  If neither is specified, a
	 constant size Gaussian will be applied to the whole image.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

@node HookHistoEqu "Hook HistoEqu"

HOOK HISTOEQU (2.0)

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Hook HistoEqu

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Run the HistoEqu hook.

